column5: Heading up to Clark's KC Landing Chain on Saturday, then at end of week doing a 2 day at Gullrock. Any fishing reports out there? I've never been on Gullrock in the fall.
Gullrock is better fishing than indian...just my thoughts. I have fished both many times. Gullrock is a superior lake to indian. You will catch plenty of good size fish out of gullrock.
I've been to Gullrock in June, what are fall patterns? I plan on bottom bouncing until I find fish - then jigging.

i used to troll with spinners all the time and it was always a hard fish in the fall, now i look at my depth finder and if i mark fish i jig . but if i;m working a flat area i will troll if the jig doesnt work.

I have always had great luck with fall fishing on gullrock. we usually go late sept. and love it. Usually look for 20-24ft of water of humps and points of course. I have fished gullrock so many times that i have my 5 to 10 spots that are my go too's. I will anchor up and jig are jig while floating with the wind. rarely troll a spinner but will at times. usual stuff.
Headed up there in a week. Anybody know the watertemps for Gullrock?
All right - fishing on the chain is slow, big temp drop overnight. Really looking forward to Saturday and Sunday at gullrock! Any recent reports or tips for September? I've only been there in June.
